# TJ-ARCH-MOB-001 compliant
# Append-only session/knowledge logs: concurrent sessions each append their own
# entries, so a "conflict" here is never a real disagreement — both sides are
# always correct and both must survive. `merge=union` keeps every line from both
# branches instead of forcing a hand-resolve on every PR.
#
# Union merge is ONLY safe for append-only, line-independent files. Do NOT extend
# this to structured files (JSON, YAML, source) where interleaving lines produces
# a syntactically broken result — progress.json is deliberately excluded.
.prometheus/events.jsonl            merge=union
.prometheus/knowledge/wiki/log.md   merge=union
.prometheus/knowledge/wiki/index.md merge=union
